This paper is about image enhancement, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of massive online photo collections for training the ranking model suggests that this paper may also belong to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The proposed approach involves learning from relatively-labeled inputs, which is a type of supervised learning, and the use of a ranking model, which suggests that this paper may also belong to machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories.
